{
  "text": "The maximal n for which such a covering occurs is n = wt + (s (The diagram is transposed compared to the convention of [CITATION_1] .) This observation shows that a northeast justified subdiagram of the (s, t)-diagram represent a (s 1 , t)-core if and only if the first wi entries in row i are not in the subdiagram for all relevant i. It would perhaps be reasonable to call such a subdigram w-shifted so that the number of possible coverings of an s-block by t-blocks equals the number of w-shifted subdiagrams of the (s, t)-diagram.",
